# Merge strategies for tracking/log files where parallel branches commonly
# append independent entries. `merge=union` concatenates both sides at conflict
# points instead of marking them as conflicts. Safe when both sides only ADD
# (never modify the same row), which is the convention for these files:
#
# - user story Devloop Tracking tables: each devloop marks its own row Complete
# - docs/TODO.md: each devloop appends its own tech-debt entries
#
# See: `infra/devloop/absorb-devloop.sh` for the automation that benefits from
# these markers.
docs/user-stories/*.md   merge=union
docs/TODO.md             merge=union
